<BLOCK1><TI TOCID="II">ORDER</TI>
<P><BOLD>THIS APPEAL</BOLD> by the <BOLD>Attorney General of Ontario, Michael Hill, and John Scott (the &ldquo;appellants&rdquo;)</BOLD> for an order: (a) setting aside the order of the Honourable Justice Wendy Matheson, dated November 29, 2016, dismissing in part the appellants' motion to strike the crossclaim brought against them by the respondents the <BOLD>Durham Regional Police Services Board, Leon Lynch, John Johnson Allan, Cindi Bradley, Daniel Anthony Denyer, Jim Burrows, Jeff Kennedy, David Kimmerly, and Dianne Jennings (the &ldquo;Durham respondents&rdquo;)</BOLD>; and (b) granting the appellant's motion to strike the crossclaim in full, was heard on January 8, 2018, at 130 Queen Street West, Toronto.</P>
<P><BOLD>ON READING</BOLD> the appeal materials filed by the appellants, the Durham respondents, and the <BOLD>York Regional Police Services Board and YRP #1 (the &ldquo;York respondents&rdquo;)</BOLD>, and on hearing the submissions of the lawyers for these parties, with no position taken by and no one appearing for the plaintiff or the defendants Her Majesty the Queen in right of Ontario, the Ontario Provincial Police, OPP #1, or OPP #2; judgement having been received to this day.
<P1><BOLD>1. THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that the Durham respondents' crossclaim against the appellants is dismissed.</P1>
<P1><BOLD>2. THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that costs of this appeal and of the motion for leave to appeal in the amount of $15,000.00 are jointly payable by the Durham respondents and York respondents to the appellants.</P1>
<P1><BOLD>3. THIS COURT ORDERS</BOLD> that costs of the motion below in the amount of $5,000.00 are jointly payable by the Durham, respondents and York respondents to the appellants.</P1></P>
<P>THIS ORDER BEARS INTEREST at the rate of 30% per year commencing on February 21<SUP>st</SUP>, 2018.</P>
<P><UNDER>SAURABH BAWEJA A/ASSISTANT REGISTRAR DIVISIONAL COURT TORONTO</UNDER></P></BLOCK1>
